	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've seen such drive doors on actual desktop PCs and on DVD players, and I even repaired one on an Apex AD-1200. The tray pushes on the door when it opens. While the tray is out, the door stays open; once the tray goes all the way back in, a spring pulls the door shut. Doors hinged in some ways might need a plastic projection glued onto them for this to work.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


